1
00:00:02,610 --> 00:00:05,010
What are AI agents?

2
00:00:05,010 --> 00:00:07,290
What are the best use cases for them?

3
00:00:07,290 --> 00:00:09,570
And what do we need to start building them?

4
00:00:09,570 --> 00:00:11,330
We're going to answer these questions

5
00:00:11,330 --> 00:00:15,250
in this first lesson of the AI agents for beginners course.

6
00:00:15,250 --> 00:00:18,250
In this course, we're going to take you from concept to code

7
00:00:18,250 --> 00:00:21,890
covering the fundamentals of building AI agents.

8
00:00:21,890 --> 00:00:23,650
And in this short video, it follows along

9
00:00:23,650 --> 00:00:26,810
with the written lesson, including translations

10
00:00:26,810 --> 00:00:29,610
and a code sample that you can find the link to

11
00:00:29,610 --> 00:00:32,090
above and below this video.

12
00:00:32,090 --> 00:00:35,210
Well, let's get started looking at the parts of an AI agent.

13
00:00:35,210 --> 00:00:37,930
And the first part is a large language model,

14
00:00:37,930 --> 00:00:45,470
which powers the reasoning behind our AI agents.

15
00:00:45,470 --> 00:00:48,110
And what we mean by reasoning is being able to identify

16
00:00:48,110 --> 00:00:51,470
a task requested by users, create a plan to complete

17
00:00:51,470 --> 00:00:55,310
that task and perform the actions of that plan.
